race.comment: Plenty of first starters with good trial form line-up - the market closer to start time holds the key. On what we have seen NAADRA (8), a Tassort filly on debut for Michael Freedman, looks hard to beat. Won a recent Randwick trial and looks to emulate Naifah, her only sibling to race, who has twice placed at stakes level. HEARTS AFFAIR (7) is a Home Affairs filly who has been to the trials twice for Gai and Adrian and finished third on each occasion. From a Savabeel mare so might get over ground in time but still comes under notice while fresh. WOLF GAP (4) is a first starter for Anthony and Sam Freedman. Recently won a Canterbury trial in good style. Nash to ride - he has only been aboard 11 runners for this stable but has won five of them. GONE TO GOWINGS (6) won a recent trial here and should acquit herself well for veteran local trainer Clarry Connors. LORAX (3) and INNER GOLD (2) are newcomers from heavyweight stables who have been well found in early betting.
